==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hickory
<hw>Hick"o*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[North American
Indian <ets>pawcohiccora</ets> (Capt. J. Smith) a kind of milk or oily
liquor pressed from pounded hickory nuts.
⟦ldquo⟧<ets>Pohickory</ets>⟦rdquo⟧ is named in a list of Virginia trees,
in 1653, and this was finally shortened to ⟦ldquo⟧hickory.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>J.
H. Trumbull.</au>]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An American tree of the
genus <gen>Carya</gen>, of which there are several species. The shagbark
is the <spn>Carya alba</spn>, and has a very rough bark; it affords the
hickory nut of the markets. The pignut, or brown hickory, is the
<spn>Carya glabra</spn>. The swamp hickory is <spn>Carya amara</spn>,
having a nut whose shell is very thin and the kernel bitter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hickory shad</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<cd>The mattowacca, or fall herring.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>The gizzard
shad.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

